3 SECTION 2. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
4 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 811 of Title 17, unless there is
5 created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
6 As used in the Renewable Energy Facility Act:
7 1. "Adjacent owner" means the landowner or landowners of
8 record of the surface estate and owners or holders of the mineral
9 estate, within a one-half (1/2) mile radius of the outer boundary of
10 any energy facility;
11 2. "Commission" means the Oklahoma Corporation Commission;
12 3. "Energy facility" means the development, construction,
13 operation, and maintenance of facilities for renewable energy
14 sources including wind energy, solar energy, battery storage,
15 hydrogen energy, or other renewable energy source, but shall not
16 include transmission or distribution lines providing services to the
17 facility;
18 4. "Facility operator" or "applicant" means a person or entity
19 who is the owner of the right to develop, operate and maintain an
20 energy facility;
21 5. "Mineral estate" means that ownership or interests as
22 defined under Section 802 of Title 52 of the Oklahoma Statutes;
23 6. "Mineral owner" means an owner or holder of certain rights
24 of the mineral estate as defined under Section 802 of Title 52 of
HB2155 HFLR Page 2
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 the Oklahoma Statutes, as to the property upon which the energy
2 facility is to be developed, operated, and maintained based upon the
3 records of the county clerk of the county within which the mineral
4 estate lies;
5 7. "Permit" means a form approved by the Commission for an
6 energy facility;
7 8. "Surface estate" means, as to any lands within the State of
8 Oklahoma, the fee simple or absolute fee ownership of a tract of
9 real property, as defined under Sections 5 and 23 of Title 60 of the
10 Oklahoma Statutes, less and excluding the mineral estate; and
11 9. "Surface owner" means the landowner or landowners of record
12 of the surface estate of the real property upon which the energy
13 facility is to be developed, operated and maintained, based upon the
14 records of the county clerk of the county within which the surface
15 estate is actually located.
16 SECTION 3. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
17 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 812 of Title 17, unless there is
18 created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
19 A. The Corporation Commission is directed and authorized to
20 promulgate rules governing the operations for energy facilities for
21 the purpose of protecting the interests and property of the citizens
22 of this state.
23 B. Any facility operator desiring to commence any energy
24 facility in this state shall, prior to commencing any such activity:
HB2155 HFLR Page 3
